# CalcMark Invalid Duration Syntax Tests

This file contains duration expressions that should FAIL to parse.

---

## Invalid Time Units

# Misspelled units
2 dyas
3 weekz
1 mounth
5 yeers

# Singular when plural expected
1 day
1 week
1 month
1 year

# Invalid abbreviations
2 d
3 w
1 mo
5 y

---

## Invalid Duration Formats

# Missing value
days
weeks
months
years

# Missing unit
2
3
10
100

# Decimal without unit
2.5
3.14

---

## Invalid Compound Durations

# Missing "and"
2 weeks 3 days
1 year 6 months 2 days
3 months 1 week

# Multiple "and" in sequence
2 weeks and and 3 days
1 year and and 6 months

# "and" without second value
2 weeks and
3 days and 

# Invalid connector
2 weeks or 3 days
1 month plus 5 days
3 weeks with 2 days

---

## Invalid Duration Arithmetic

# Negative durations (syntax level)
-2 days
-3 weeks

# Duration operators that don't make sense
2 days * 3
3 weeks / 2
1 month % 5

# Duration with duration (instead of date)
2 days + 3 weeks
1 month - 2 weeks

---

## Edge Cases

# Zero duration
0 days
0 weeks

# Very large numbers (syntax OK, semantic may validate)
# (These might actually be valid syntax)

# Mixed types in compound
2 days and 3
1 week and
